-- Cinda Asset Management to Seek Domestic Share Listing, China Daily Says
-- Mark Lee
-- 2010-07-17T01:46:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-17/cinda-asset-management-to-seek-domestic-share-listing-china-daily-says.html

          
          
             China Cinda Asset Management Co.
plans to list shares on a domestic exchange, China Daily
reported, citing President Tian Guoli. The company aims to
attract financial firms as strategic investors, the English-
language newspaper cited Tian as saying. Cinda, a manager of
distressed assets, was turned into a stock-holding company on
July 16 after a reorganization, according to the report. The
company is wholly owned by the finance ministry, the paper said.  
